Una unitat 6000 de TMB entrant a l'estació de Catalunya de la línia L1 del metro de Barcelona, fent un servei entre Fondo i Hospital de Bellvitge. L'estació de Catalunya del denominat Metro Transversal es va posar en servei el 1932 (provisionalment el 1926 entre rambla Catalunya i Balmes), trobant-se les dues vies del metro laterals a les dues vies del ferrocarril, que té una andana central. Antigament l'espai era diàfan i es podien veure en un mateix espai les vies del metro i del ferrocarril, amb un vestíbul al costat Passeig de Gràcia i un altre al costat Rambla de Catalunya. Els anys 1980 es va haver de reforçar tota l'estructura i es va construir el gran vestíbul actual conjunt metro-ferrocarril. El 1992 es va reformar tota l'estació (18.06.2019) #metro #metrodebarcelona #barcelona #tmb #caf #linia1 #l1 #subway #underground #catalunya #catalonia #trenscat

Podría quedarme horas parada en la ventana escuchando las sirenas de los bomberos y los bocinazos y puteadas de los autos que pasan por Bowery, viendo a la gente caminar torpemente y mezclándome rapidito entre ellos. Revolviendo ropa vintage convencida de que estoy destinada a encontrar un tesoro escondido. Tomando los cafés más horribles que probé en mi vida y volcándome encima uno de los más ricos. Revolcándome en Central Park con seis chihuahuas. Viendo a las moscas y las abejas bailar, y a las ardillas jugar a la estatuas. Saludando a todas las flores que me crucé. Quedándome trabada en el molinete del subte porque hice pasar primero a la valija y riéndome con la gente que me vio hacer semejante pavada. Comiendo zanahorias en todos lados hasta que me pudrí y me animé a sentarme a comer en lugares sin poder parar. Diciéndole mi número de habitación al chico del front desk durante 13 días hasta que me pidió disculpas y se lo aprendió de memoria. Caminando desde Soho hasta Central Park en zigzag por Broadway y la 5ta. Corriendo descalza en el pasto. Perdiéndome por el barrio hasta encontrarme. Dejar a un actor hablarme al oído, saboreando el olor a chocolate de su sangre falsa. Indicándole a un señor que me dijo “ma’am” para qué lado quedaba Canal Street sin saber donde estaba parada. Sentándome a leer en todos lados y cruzando miradas entre las hojas. Amando. Durmiendo la siesta al sol. Riéndome entre desconocidos. Creciendo. 
Creí que me iba el viernes cuando en realidad me voy el jueves y no puedo parar de llorar porque me tengo que despedir de golpe. Fue un viaje largo y hermoso que sigue en casa, acá voy a volver.

Sin duda estos azulejos marcan tendencia tanto en baños como en cocinas, ya que no sólo son un revestimiento sino también un elemento de diseño.
.
.
Este tipo de azulejos comenzó  a usarse para las primeras estaciones de subte de grandes ciudades como por ejemplo Paris ( a partir del 1900), seguida por Londres, NY y Madrid. .
.
Brindan una estética amplia y luminosa y son ideales para acompañar con elementos decorativos como plantas de interior y madera, ya que esto hace que contrarreste el efecto frío de la cerámica. Además, son súper sencillos y fáciles de limpiar!
.

TIPS!! Coconut flour Flatbread! 
So tasty and easy to make! ✨
I love healthy eating but I also love cooking easy and delicious recipes! This is exactly that! You don’t need any mixer, just mix all the ingredients with a table spoon and your flatbread will be ready, in only 25min🤩
I was extremely bloated all last week. Then I made this delicious flatbread with a Psyllium Husk (twice) and my stomach has returned to normal again! Psyllium Husk does wonders!! Psyllium is a form of fiber made from the husks of the Plantago ovata plant’s seeds. It helps promote regularity and overall digestive health. I highly recommending it 😉 if you feel bloated or constipated 🙃
Here are the ingredients and the instructions if you’re willing to try them ;) Ingredients:
1/2 cup Coconut flour
2 tablespoons Psyllium Husk powder
1/4 cup Coconut oil (or melted butter)
1/2 teaspoon Salt
1 teaspoon Baking powder
1 Cup Boiling water
Herbs/garlic powder to flavour optional

Instructions:
Mix the dry ingredients with a hand whisk.
Add the oil and blend well. It will look like a nut butter.
Add the boiling water, half at a time and blend until a dough like mixture forms.
Divide the mixture into 6 balls.
Roll the balls between 2 sheets of parchment paper and flatten out.
Either use them flattened or cut them into a circle with a saucepan lid.
Dry fry in a pan for 2– 3 minutes each side, until golden.

Steve was in there almost daily because “there was nothing in the fridge”. It’s where I ran in dressed to see no one, only to find everyone. A corporate entity but a community centre. All good things come in threes. So do our products, as they have three certifications. Do you know what they represent? 👀 The first one is ​@allergycertified One of their criteria is that the allergy-causing nickel has to be below 1ppm (0.0001%) in makeup. Nickel is found as an impurity in the colours used for makeup. With a number this low, the nickel doesn’t harm anyone, even if you are allergic to nickel. 💪🏼 Also, our products don’t contain any perfumes and the raw materials are very pure and gentle. This certification guarantee that our products are as allergy-friendly as they can be and you can feel good using them! ✔️😇💙•
•
Vi har tre certificeringer på vores produkter. Men ved du egentlig, hvad de betyder? 👀 Den første er @allergycertified Et af deres krav er, at indholdet af allergifremkaldende Nikkel i makeup skal være under 1 ppm (0,0001 %). Nikkel findes som urenheder i farvestoffer i makeup. Ved så lavt indhold, så kan vi alle tåle det, også selvom du måske er allergisk overfor nikkel. 💪🏼 Derudover indeholder vores produkter ikke parfume og råvarerne er rene og skånsomme. Today Boise Celebrates the 30th annual pride festival! It all started 1 year after I was born, and I must say, our teenagers live in a world far different than the one I grew up in, and I now understand the work of generations before me. Today I get to do something that was unthinkable 20 years ago. Today I get to be visible as not only a gay man, but as an LGBT face in the Boise-based Albertsons grocer family. I stand with my local store level colleagues with excitement that we can be who we are in all aspects of our life. As a corporate level employee of Albertsons Companies, I also stand on behalf of my nationwide peers who work under our various banner names in areas that aren't as loving and accepting as our Boise, ID. Whether you show it in public, or see it in the mirror, I pray that everyone finds pride in who they are, and always chooses love and acceptance over hate and judgement. Happy 30th Pride Day, Boise!

🌲Humility🌲 More on this one (see June 11th also) When I was younger, the thought of a humble person always brought to mind an old man, bowing down to those he saw as greater than himself -a person almost beaten down and made to feel small. I don’t see it like that anymore. I now believe that true humility is about maintaining integrity, yet always being willing to learn. Humility not as timidity, but extending a loving, open heart to possibility. I am not religious, but I do find a lot of beauty and wisdom in some religious texts. An example of true humility would be the story of Jesus washing his disciples feet: “If I then, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet, you also ought to wash one another's feet. For I have given you an example, that you should do as I have done to you. Most assuredly, I say to you, a servant is not greater than his master; nor is he who is sent greater than he who sent him. If you know these things, blessed are you if you do them. — John 13:14–17 (NKJV)

I find it a very sweet sentiment. Shadowland by Peter Straub is the coming of age story of Tom and Del who meet at a prestigious boarding school.
.
The structure of the book splits it into two main parts. The first being the time spent at the boarding school and the events which take place there setting up the creepy and eerie vision of what Shadowland is about and then there is the second part set at Coleman Collins home. A house made of secret doorways and traps which lure the boys to learn about real magic and what’s really happing in Shadowland.
.
Initially I thought this would be a horror novel but the further I read the more it was obvious its a fantasy one with horror elements. It’s been said that you could compare it slightly to Stephen King’s IT and on some level I suppose you could as the similar factor of Shadowland being of magic, the beings that dwell there, give off that familiar feeling. This book was written in 1980, where the idea of young magicians finding each other to then go on to defeat a sorcerer was fairly new.
.
The imagery was quite gruesome and shocking on a few occasions. There is a specific badger scene which had me quite surprised, some of the scenes that take place in Shadowland felt like you were on some kind of a trip. Those elements were well written. The first part of the book gave a good build up however it felt like it lagged on more than one occasion. There’s no doubt that the fantasy themes are heavily present throughout, I wouldn’t go as far as saying it was terrifying, this could also be because I’ve read it as an adult, had I read it in my teens maybe I would have felt differently.
.
The book has received some harsh criticism over not being as iconic as Ghost Story (which i’ve yet to read), I wouldn’t say its a bad novel at all, it was a good read, and if I had to score it out of 5 I would give it a 3.75.
.

Путешественники от Бога или как остаться без денег в Крыму.

2 года назад мы с подругой купили билет в один конец, сделав выбор в пользу Крыму из-за дешёвых цен. Уезжая, две мадам часть денег припрятали в носочки, оставшуюся часть в надёжные банки.

Ни в коем случае не берите пример с этих дам 😀
✅Во-первых, отдельно билеты обратно стоят в 3 раза дороже.
✅Во-вторых, не со всех карт вы снимите деньги в банкомате, а если и снимете то с комиссией. О чём мы узнали на месте, когда у одной очень умной мадам оказалась карта Citibanka, а у второй ещё более умной пришел счёт за комиссию 1000 рублей за частичное снятие денег.
✅Также нельзя перевести деньги через Western Union, поскольку Крым отключен от системы международных переводов SWIFT. Для этого вам придётся ехать в Краснодар.

Так что планируя путешествие в Крым запаситесь носочками и обналичьте побольше средств.

С банками тут очень плохо.
➡Привычных нам российских банков там нет.
➡Не все банки принимают российские карты.
➡Есть местные банки "РНКБ" и "ГЕНБАНК" они принимают большинство карт, карту Сбербанка принимают точно, но будьте внимательны с некоторых карт снимают процент за обналичивание.

Поэтому если обналичивание деньги в местом банке, то снимайте сразу всю сумму которая вам нужна иначе за каждую операцию у вас будут списывать комиссию ✅Сбербанк -  1%  не менее 100  рублей
✅Тинькофф банк – при  снятии  не менее 3000 рублей – без комиссии, менее 3 тыс. рублей– 90 рублей
✅Альфа Банк -1,25% не менее 150 руб.
✅Райфайзен банк- 100-150 руб. (зависит от типа карты) +1%

Нельзя снять деньги с карт:
➡Иностранных
➡Citibank
➡Сбербанка "Моментум" и "Социальная"

P.S. А вы знали что шелест пересчитываемых банкнот 💱💱💱, который мы слышим, снимая деньги в банкомате, не настоящий. Купюры перед выдачей пересчитываются, но услышать это нельзя. Практика первых банкоматов показала, что клиенты нервничают, если после того, как они ввели свои данные, ничего не происходит.

#christmasbreak 2000, I took a one month #leaveofabsence from #work because mom was ill. I had been banking with #citibank since I first arrived in #manhattan . My #landlady who suggested me to open up a #bankaccount .

There was no problem. They only asked a minimum of $100 to open up an account. 
I returned home permanently the end of 2001. In January 2002, Citibank called and said there had been a change of #policy , unless I could increase my #savingsaccount to the new minimum balance of $5000, they had no choice but closing my account by the end of the month. 
I didn't know  there were so many rich people in the beloved country of mine who could maintain minimum of 5 grand, considering the #exchangerate was quite high. (and still is) Rp.15000, = $1 only approximately. 
So I withdrew the #money and went to #localbank .

They asked for Rp.500,000 surely I could do that. However, my #identitycard was just a bit , I repeat slightly ruined by watermark that affected the end of my #signature marking although it was still very visible.

The super 'nice' #customerservice in front of me said sorry my #application is denied. I said to her, look.everything matches with the #passport yes? With signature intact and all the rest of the information matched.  Dob , name etc.

She said no. Sorry

Oh. Alright then. Bye.thanks for your #senseandsensibility

My mom was using that bank for as long as I could remember. After father passed away, she asked me to put my name in her account as join account (?) in case something happened.

When I got a #check from overseas, I couldn't #cash it.

I could no longer remember what were their excuses, but I closed the #account right away because what is the function of #banking #system if their clients couldn't cash in a check????? Do tell. Because I am confused. Are you ?

These free credit cards are all great cards to get once you have gotten you credit score over the 700 mark. All of these cards except for my honorable mention are cards that I personally use.

1. The Uber credit card is an amazing card to use and keep in your daily line up, it provide you with 4% back on dining, 3% back on hotels and airfare, 2% online, and 1% on everything else. This card also has a $100 signing Bono’s after you spend $500 on it. This cards rewards on dining makes it by far one of the best free cards you can have.

2. The Capital One Quicksilver is a great general spend card with 1.5% back on everything. If you spend $300 they will reward you with a $100 signing bonus.

3. The Amazon Prime card is the perfect card for any amazon junky to have. The card provide 5% back on all purchases on amazon. It also has a $70 gift card for signing up for it.

HONORABLE MENTION

The City double is a great general spend card to have, you get 2% back on everything. One percent when you purchase something and one more when you pay it off. The only reason this does not beat out the Capital One Quicksilver is that is has no signing bonus. To out earn the Quicksilver and it’s rewards you would have to spend over $10,000 on it.

Bitcoin é o MELHOR e MAIS JUSTO dinheiro que existe. Você
acha que a frase é ousada? Te desafio a dedicar algumas horas paraestudá-lo e rejeitar a frase, se você ainda acha que é ousada.
.
Os bitcoins são, em essência, dinheiro digital. O dinheiro usado parafazer pagamentos de forma barata e muito rápida em todo o planeta, sema necessidade de bancos ou cartões de crédito.
.
Essas moedas são
gerenciadas pelo software chamado Bitcoin da mesma maneira.
.
Dinheiro programável, dinheiro de código aberto, protocolo de pagamento distribuído, … há muitos termos relacionados a ele e, nos capítulos seguintes, você entenderá detalhadamente por quê.
.
O Bitcoin separa completamente dinheiro e política e é global. Isso
significa que, pela primeira vez na história, existe um dinheiro pode queser realmente usado e que é fácil de usar, que dá às pessoas liberdadeabsoluta por não depender de uma moeda administrada por políticas
econômicas decididas por organizações pseudo-privadas ou bancoscentrais.
.
O Bitcoin está transformando o sistema financeiro global.
O Bitcoin é gratuito, aberto e suas moedas não são emitidas por nenhumbanco, governo ou empresa, tendo claras vantagens sobre o dinheiroemitido pelos bancos centrais e até mesmo com o ouro. Funciona graçasa uma rede de milhares de computadores, sendo hoje a rede decomputadores mais poderosa e segura do mundo.
.
.

É um facto que o Bitcoin veio para ficar. Uma tecnologia que une
pessoas eliminando intermediários que não fornecem nenhum valor.
Como você pode ver, a tecnologia subjacente ao bitcoin é realmente
incrível.
.
Esta tecnologia está em seus primeiros passos e qualquer um podeparticipar ativamente de qualquer frente: Difusão, Consumo,
Desenvolvimento.
.
Uma das analogias que melhor explicam sua relevância é a seguinte: “Bitcoin é para o dinheiro o que Internet foi para informação”
.
Os economistas vêm investigando o comportamento das pessoas por séculos: como nós
tomamos decisões como agimos individualmente e em grupo, e como fazemosintercâmbio de Valores, estudam como facilitar nossas interações pelo sistema legal,
corporações e o mercado.
.
Como humanos, buscamos maneiras de reduzir as incertezas uns sobre os outros de
modo a podermos beneficiar da troca de valores.
.

Next in the NFC North are the Minnesota Vikings. The Vikings have an elite defense, ranking 9th in points allowed and 4th in yards allowed last year. They have an elite secondary with Harrison Smith and Xavier Rhodes, and a great pass rusher in Danielle Hunter. Eric Kendricks is a very underrated linebacker. The offense is good as well, with a great RB in Dalvin Cook, a threatening WR duo in Stefon Diggs and Adam Thielen, and a great TE in Kyle Rudolph. The only reason I have them behind the final two teams in this division is because of the quarterback position.

Sometimes I see simple scenes like this and I realise that I'm often so caught up with my fixed schedule and my tightly-packed life that I forget that there is beauty in taking some time to relax. I forget that there is a world outside of huddling around my laptop as I eat a quick supper, and that there are places for me find a change of pace if only I would bother to open my eyes. This past week has been hard on me in that I've had more anxieties to deal with and made more mistakes than I would've liked. Still, there have been a few beautiful drops of sunshine dispersed throughout that've made the week that little bit easier to bear. Hopefully, this coming week and the rest of the quarter will be more about me finding a balance in my life and doing better in everything I'm a part of. To everyone else who is having a hard time, I wish you all the best, and may you always find time to appreciate the little moments when you get the chance to witness the grand beauty of life. #SunsetRec #UCLA #MassOnTheGrass #JustSundayThings #randomthoughts #lifeisbeautiful

J'avais tellement hâte de vous montrer le résultat de ce projet oriental 😍💃🙌 !!
Voici la première photo qui est l'un de mes coups de cœur 💗 même si je vous avoue en avoir eu plein d'autres dans la sélection 😍 ce fut compliqué pour choisir... 😅
Je suis hyper ravie d'avoir participé à ce projet qu'Emilie m'avait proposé l'année dernière, on a formé une très belle équipe féminine ❤️
C'est elle qui a créé expressément ce magnifique costume pour ce projet et qui est l'auteur de ce superbe décor oriental 😍 (je suis venue l'aider le premier jour du montage et je peux vous dire qu'il y a des heures et des heures de boulot derrière et que ce ne fut pas simple du tout pour monter tout ça, il y a un travail de couleurs, de hauteur, de profondeur et de relief monstre derrière cette photo, on ne s'imaginerait pas en regardant cette image mais oui ça a pris 2 jours pour mettre en place juste le décor ✌️😅 beaucoup de réflexion aussi hahaha n'est-ce pas Émilie ? 😅 Mine de rien j'ai adoré pouvoir participer au montage d'un décor, je pense que c'était une première pour moi 🤔) ainsi que de cette image car elle est non seulement une styliste et une créatice de décor hors pair mais en plus une photographe bourrée de talent et je tenais à le dire ✨🎑 pour compléter l'équipe, il y avait ma fidèle et talentueuse @floz_gtgbr à la coiffure ✂ 😍🤗 et @melissa_muabe au makeup une nouvelle et très belle rencontre artistique d'ailleurs 🎨💄
Bref ! Ça faisait longtemps que j'avais fait un aussi beau projet et ça me redonne goût & motivation à en refaire même si j'ai beaucoup moins de temps par rapport à avant 🤗💪
Vous êtes au TOP les filles, ne changez rien et merciiiii encore à toutes les 3 pour votre magnifique travail, j'ai passé une magnifique journée ☀️ !
Ça m'a beaucoup plu de me mettre dans la peau d'une danseuse orientale le temps d'un shooting, on avait mit de la musique typiquement orientale d'ailleurs pour se mettre dans l'ambiance, j'ai juste adoré ♥️
Mercii encore à toi Émilie vraiment 🙏🙌
